@node "Intro" "Short Introduction"
 @{b}@{u}The HTML - Filter@{ub}@{uu}

This @{b}@{i}little@{ub}@{ui} Progam allows you to Filter @{b}all@{ub} HTML-Codes out af an HTML-Text so
you can work with the plain ASCII-Text.
@endnode

@node "Working" "How does it work ?"
@{b}@{u}The HTML-Filter@{ub}@{uu} -> How does it work.

I don`t think you`ll need this information `coz the tool is quite easy to use
- but here come the steps.

 1. Load a HTML-Text from your Disk

 2. The HTML-Filter will start it`s work just after loading the HTML-Text

 3. When the processing-bar has reached the 100% you can save the plain
    ASCII-text whereever you want :)

 That`s all Folks !


@{b}@{u}Attention:@{ub}@{uu}
 You can also start HTML-Filter from DOpus/CLI with this command:

                     @{b}HTML-Filter@{ub} @{i}@{fg shine}filename@{ui}@{fg text}
@endnode

